<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Doubt, pity, and weakness.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sufferage for the Weak.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Part 1.<br>
What do you expect when you fight the Hopeless Battle?<br>
<br>
<br>
The Arena is where it always leaves. The Trueness of what really goes on, beyond hatefilled words and worthless religious batter, what really defines a person is his weapon, and what he can do with it. Soul and Sword.<br>
<br>
When the words stop flying.. this, the Arena, is where one it supposed to put up, or be tossed to the wayside with the rest of the Trash.<br>
<br>
It was rape. Pure and simple, for their is no other word for it. The Members of Fire and Fury laughed as their power stood abounded. Ogarth wasn't even there. He didn't have to be.<br>
To live and die a thousand times is an experence that would bring even the most faithful doubting their gods, or even the most hardened warrior doubting the ability to handle his own blade.<br>
<br>
Blast after blasted raped him of his pride. Slash after slash ravished him of his purpose. Death after death stole away his sprit. They laughed and cheered after every one. This was no contest for them. He lived for longer then many of these people. Some in the croud he saw began younger then him, but throught the help of the power that combining all classes, creeds, and races brings to a guild, they grew much much stronger then he could ever see himself being. Even if he had Innoruuk's curse, one blast from their hands again raped him of his very being. <br>
<br>
The Nightmare is often worse then the reality, and in the blur he saw them all. All that ever turned their back to go to it, all that ever was born within it, and those that corrupted and turned people to it. Neutrality was a stronger curse upon the land then the Paladins of light could ever be.<br>
<br>
After the many hours he spent during the rape, it was over. beaten, burned, and defeated completly and totally, he saw how truly high that mountain was. He could never even begin to climb. That day something did die inside of him, more or less something taken. <br>
<br>
No longer was he able to continue on. No matter how much he preached, no matter how long he faught, they would not listen. Always those that could make a true difference would leave to join them. The point became lost within the dispear and realization of what is true.<br>
<br>
He was just another Halfbreed playing ShadowKnight.<br>
<br>
The fights from there do not matter really. Defeated by Xaenria, but his sprit had already been raped away by the Fury. He saw the power of the Neutrals first hand, and their was nothing he could do about it.<br>
<br>
So he let it die, right there, guild banner and all! He threw all that made him that falsity, that fake Legend Knight known only as 'Shintou Shinai' ~ The Insane Slaughter of Elves. All that remained was a small child. Eyes wide to the world, alone, and afraid.<br>
<br>
Kestrel pleaded to no avail. Her words fell upon the ears of a man no longer the master of hate, but dominated and chained by its force. The struggle to control and use hate to ones advtange had crushed and destroyed what was there.<br>
<br>
Faentriel and Mudwart met the same resistance. Even Despa wondered why.<br>
<br>
Apep had been expecting it however. He had been taking the members of the league that wanted power lately, at the cost of their souls and survatude to his Castle Storm, and the Barbarians as well as Vah Shir which keep that house Neutralic.<br>
<br>
He didn't get another Soul in Kenshin. He turned him down before he could open his mouth. With a simple statement, uncharaistically calm and consience.<br>
<br>
&quot;I cannot join you, that I cannot. I have no reason to, that I don't. You know that that you do.&quot;<br>
<br>
He ended that claim. Shockening enought, the old Mage expected it and simply nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Even now, you're still too damned stubborn.&quot;<br>
<br>
And then, the days began to pass. Times he felt what died within him trying to revive.. he had throught that he could sit in the Plane of Tranquility and live in a state of constant meditation. But sometimes, old habits are hard to forget. He had to occupy his mind.<br>
He had to occupy his blade. He did it in the way he would always. Sate himself by doing simple tasks, the one currently to gain total and complete Alliance with the Overthere Outpost, in the blood of Sarnak Bezerkers. This was enought to occupy himself as he lived throught the mizery that was his life.<br>
<br>
And the days passed.. till their was Kaileena.<br>
She appeared before him finally, forcing him to meet her in Neriak.<br>
<br>
The heart of the girl had been shattered. Number 4, if you are counting. He never truly did realize his mastery of breaking the hearts of lovers, now did he. Her words, rushed and edged with the fires of hate. Had he still been Shintou, maybe he would of been impressed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I won't let you give up! You didn't let me ever give up, so I won't allow you to!&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I love you! Can't you see that! How can you leave me!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;All of my teachings were lies, Kaileena. Forget them as you forget me, and maybe you will come into strenght.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No! You will not give up! I swear to Innoruuk I'll kill you if you do!&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Love me or die! You cannot run out on me! What kind of a man are you! Love me or feel the sting of my shattered heart!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That is when Shintou turned his back and started walking away. He knew Kaileena would come with a hard direct stab to his spine. He taught her the move. It was easy to see it comming, and it was even eaiser to shadowstep away from it. After that the battle went quickly. He slain his own student there in cold blood, almost without the same mercy or remorse that Shintou gave his opponets, but without the same Malious Cruelty or the True Joy that was taken in the Slaughter.<br>
<br>
&quot;When you return, you will maybe then learn to forget me, and your worthless love.&quot; Were the words he spoke over her shaking body as he walked away, leaving her behind as he had left so much before.<br>
<br>
And their was more.<br>
Within the Faydark is where he ended up. The League of Shadows against the League of Honor. But that was not the reason he came. He came to search for someone, someone he knew that would have something for him, answers to a new search now, one he figured out during the various battles with the Sarnaks.<br>
<br>
The war was just a bit of Enterainment, so he figured. Untill Quinrooss. The Human Cleric brought him into the battle. He saw throught his shadows and demanded a fight.<br>
<br>
Damn that Priest. I'll become Shintou just for you.<br>
<br>
But Shintou was already ravished, wounded, raped, and destroyed. He had no chance in a battle, even against a Cleric. Defeated by one that was at his own Season.<br>
<br>
Another sign, that darkness.. that HE was comming to an end.<br>
<br>
Their was Kulligen, full with hate. The Entire League, shouting in one unaminous voice.<br>
&quot;HalfBreed go Home! Wait, you are home! Worthless HalfBreed! You will die!&quot; the shouts of their dead souls to him.<br>
It was the first time that he felt himself being called that. He earned it, after all.<br>
<br>
Kullgen went after Kenshin with her fists, trying to strike him down with just those and her spells. It was working too, For Kenshin didn't use his spells, he was much higher in level then she. This was just a fight, he only had one message.<br>
He knew Innoruuk was working, and working quickly. <br>
He caught her fists, right after she unleashed a Harm Touch to him, one leaving him barley holding on to life.<br>
<br>
And he spoke to her, one final time.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kaileena will rise again. When she does, teach her to be the Knight that I never was. Also, teach her to be the Tier'dal Woman you are. This is my final request of you!&quot; He said as the relfex kicked in.<br>
<br>
Old habits die hard. And a Harm Touch is always met with a Harm Touch. The Malious Hand of Lanys stuck Kulligen in the chest. Her eyes rolled back. For the night.. she was out.<br>
<br>
Shintou baded Ayemi to finish it, the Priest could do in two blasts.<br>
And she nodded, doing as he wished. Upon this death, he saw a flash.<br>
<br>
The Father was watching. His grin was wide. That was when he knew that he was right. Innoruuk is in control, he shall always be. Halfbreed or not, throught his mother Kenshin was still bound.<br>
To the Father, to the Mother. Innoruuk watched his bastard son well.<br>
When he woke, their was Shaveil to talk to. But after that was finished, Shaveil only nodded.<br>
<br>
Still a friend, the two shook hands. After that, Shintou was gone. Deep within the Faydark, he saught out the one with his answers.<br>
<br>
He knew Innoruuk would always be in control. But he also knew he could never fight again, with the memories of that night.<br>
<br>
One night at the arena. The one that finally raped and destroyed his life. When the true power of the Neutralic Machine was hammered down on him.<br>
Just like in the plane of Justice.<br>
He was found ...lacking.<br>
<br>
He did find what he searched for, finding the bouncy Druid.<br>
In his eyes, she was the cloest thing..<br>
<br>
..To the Avatar of Tunare. She welcomed him with a smile and a nod. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come, sit with me. Ask me anything. I will grant you peace. Seperate yourself from the world, and begin to find yourself within my forest.&quot;<br>
<br>
She didn't say it, that Druid did not. She did give him advice, various things to help him, for like Tunare, this Druid loved all things. The one that said that was Tunare, for he heard her voice intertwined with that Druid.<br>
<br>
&quot;Find yourself, not one shrouded by masks or hidden away by emotions of self pity. Who is Kenshin, it was so long when your parents were killed and Yoto.. no when You created Shintou to hide from the loss of your loved ones that you truly do not even know yourself.&quot; Said Tunare.<br>
<br>
The Druid rambled on, and did silly things, like headstands and danced and.. did what druids do.<br>
<br>
And when she didn't speak, he continued to meditate in the Faydark.<br>
<br>
Tunares voice spoke in his ears. The voice did not outrightfully say it, for it forced him to do nothing. It just said find yourself, over and over.<br>
<br>
Who am I?<br>
<br>
