<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Doubt, pity, and weakness.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sufferage for the Weak.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Part 2.<br>
The Search for Kenshin.<br>
<br>
The Overthere, small rolling hills, a deep chasum.. and sarnacks.. with whips. What else is there? Oh, a huge Outpost Built with the combined efforts of The Dead, Mayong Mistimoore, Vernil Sathir, and the Dark Relfection.  In this place, the evilist of evils.. is where we find out little guy, Kenshin Kintanka.<br>
<br>
He knelt down, opening up a jar which he retrieved from the bank just down the way. That jar contained a pretty vengeful sprit, a sprit of a man who watched his entire family get slaughtered before him. This sprit who had to watch the destiny which was to befall him befall another, added with the complete fustration of this soul. Yotoden formed before him, even with his sword, Fujikuro.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where did you place my father, Yotoden.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You summoned me for this? Are you not ready to form the souledge with my sprit?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Their's been a change of plans that their has. I won't be going after the Innoruuk's Curse anymore I do not think. I'm not your puppet Shintou Shinai anymore, that I am not. I've broken your insanity, Yotoden, that I have.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You fool! Do you know how long it took me to train you? And you go ahead and undo all of that!?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll never be strong enought to do anything unless I face up to what has been keeping me weak. Their is something in my heart, something unsolved. Shintou Shinai, that was just a mask to keep myself from this thing. I no longer wear masks, you see. I want the truth, now where is my father!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;As if I'll ever tell you. I can see it in your eyes, you've become the worthless halfbreed child. Maybe I should start calling you Kenshin from now on, boy.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You forget.&quot; Kenshin spoke, clasping his hands together then pulling them apart, a field of mana energy forming inbetween them, sparkling green. &quot;I am still a ShadowKnight, that I am. Innoruuk hasn't stripped me of my ability to use spells yet. I can still destroy your soul, and without it you would not exist, that you would not. Tell me what I want to know, and you will be free.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why go after your parents, Kenshin. I can tell you everything you wish to know right here, I watched you grow before I took you to Lavastorm and taught you the ways of Insanity. Here, I will be---&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Shut your mouth! I think you've told me enought lies about myself, that you have!&quot; Kenshin said harshly, the field of energy forming into a ball, and beginning to spin. &quot;You have one more chance. Tell me where you slain my father or I will destroy you, that I will.&quot;<br>
<br>
And the fear finally faded shown in the eyes of Yotoden. He knew the boy was serious.. he did beat him in combat back then.. and now he held dominion over his soul.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are a fool for giving up the power. Had you gotten the Innoruuk's Curse, you would of been Invinable. Your Father was slain outside of the spiers, right after he took your mother in the Faydark. I didn't allow him to live long after he served his purpose. I told the Guards there what he did, so they did not give him a proper elven Burial. Whilest they do not know that the Tier'dal had a child to him, they did know that he was cruel. He was tossed on the side, the hill there and allowed to rott. Your Mother, after she was slain by the Guards was tossed in the place where all Dishonored Tier'dal go. By her letting you survive, halfbreed, the City of Neriak deemed her worthless and dishonored. You see, back then, even the halfbreeds were slaughtered by the City. Now of course, they allow all who wish to enter enter by killing some halflings or getting that guy Drunk down in the Libarary. If you were born some many years eariler, you might of had a chance. Your Step-Father was tossed aside just like your mother.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Step Fathe.. I guess I will have to find out now won't I? That I will. Thank you, old sprit of the dead. Yotoden, you are free to go that you are.&quot; And with that, Kenshin shattered the jar which held the sprit of Yotoden in place for so many years, turning his mana energy upon it instead of Yotoden himself. The sprit faded away to the spectral realm, a smile upon his face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you.&quot; Yotoden said as it faded away into the light.<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
The Greater Faydark.<br>
<br>
Kenshin stood before the spiers, taking 20 or paces away from them before putting his hands together and falling to his knees.<br>
<br>
It would be easy to pick out the Soul which belonged to his Elven Father and force it to come.. but that Druid from before told him that maybe he should simply ask nicely for them to come. Those that wish to come will. So he asked, but yet he did not recieve. A Soft plea to speak with the man who birthed him fell upon deaf ears. Maybe he was running from what he did as well. This is the time when force was applied. He summoned the sprit much like he would summon an undead minion, forcing the Ranger to come up and face him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You. There you are.&quot; Kenshin spoke, standing to face his father. &quot; I am ---&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Their is no damned need to speak your name, I know what you are. You are what I created. Innoruuk torments my soul by making me watch you as you kill and slaughter my kind, those that were my legimimate children! How can you be so cruel, Shintou!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You may know what I am, but you do not know who I am apparently. That is not my name, my name is Kenshin that it is. I have saught you out to understand.. why? Why did you not just kill my mother? Why did you do this to me? You may torment as I used to slaughter your breathern without mercy, but I suffered daily by what you did! Are you followers of Tunare not peaceful and kind? You destroyed my life, that you did. Because of you, I cannot truly be Shintou Shinai, that I cannot. I am damned because of you, dammed because of your blood that I share! So tell me why!?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Heh.. hah..&quot; Shintou the Ranger broke into a laughter. His laugh echoing throughtout the forest as an undead houl. &quot;I did it because I knew how best to ensure that she'd never bother me again. You were supposed to become soft and shame them both, a Tier'dal follower of Tunare. Back then, that would of been ironic, however common it now is. That damned Yotoden interfeared with my seed and drove you insane, I see that now. Kenshin now is it? I enjoyed it, too.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You sir are more evil and vile then Shintou Shinai could of ever been, that you are. And I do not feel generous enought to allow your sprit to survive, that I do not. No wonder that you were the source of his darkness.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So you'll destroy my soul like a Paladin on a Crusade. Not very Shintou Shinaiish of you, now is it boy.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You forgot, that is not my name that it is NOT!&quot; he shouted as he casted the same spell, one that strikes at the very ki of the undead, blasting him with the dismiss undead spell, it slowly, painfully destroying the sprit of Kenshin's Father.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your sprit will die, that it will. You shall no longer exist, that you shall not. Curse you for what you have done to me. Those women who loved me could never recieve that love in return because of how you cursed me. I could never understand them, so I had to let them go, that I did. You damned me to a life of weakness, that you did. Always battling hate and unable to fully allow it to power me like Havvok or Kullgen or Tallonar or any other knight could. You robbed me of that, and thats what brings me here to destroy your soul, that it does. You brought this on yourself, that you did.&quot; <br>
<br>
He said as he watched the final trindils of the Rangers sprit fade from Norrath. That was settled. He confronted what he throught to be the source of his Hatred and destroyed it with one simple blast.<br>
<br>
So he figured.<br>
<br>
