<br>
Part 3.<br>
What you miss you can never truly forget.<br>
<br>
The Nektulos forest, unlike the forest of the Faydark is filled with the wispers of the undead. Their soft howls fill this forest with a frightening aura that seems to caress the trees and run along the ground. In this place, their seems to be an espically strong amount of undead.. this resting place of the dishonored and disrespected. The Tier'dal who were not strong enought to be Tier'dal back in those days were dumped here to beforgotten, as wastes..<br>
<br>
&quot;I know you are here Mother. Come, please. I would like to see you with my own eyes, instead of hearing from you by stories laced with lies, that I do. Come before me, every child should at least get to see their mother. This is not like the last times, when I forced your soul from the realm of sprit, but this time I ask you. I wish to speak to you, that I do.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kenshin sat on his knees, wearing only his shade silk robe he prayed and waited.. and soon enought a pair of sprits did come before him.. one female, one male. The Females sprit seemed to glow in a faint purple light, the color of her eyes. Her hair was short, only comming up to the back of her neck at best. She still wore her armor, and wielded her sword, the 'Dark Reaver'. Back then, it was a seemingly strong weapon, now of course .. we know better. <br>
<br>
The Male who held her free hand held a staff. His robes were dark red in color, as were the color of his eyes. He glanced over to Isabella with a questioning look. As if to say..<br>
&quot;Should we even be here? Why?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh Raziel. Look at him. Kenshin's all grown up. You can't tell me you weren't curious to see how he would grow.&quot; The female spoke, nodding to the Male who simply just turned his gase upon the boy.<br>
<br>
&quot;But Isabella, you've been watching him ever since you died. I always catch you watching him.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah? Well I caught you too, Raz.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thats ENOUGHT!&quot; Kenshin shouted to the sprits, his hands already blue with the undead killing spell. &quot;I called you here to talk to me, not talk amonst yourselves! .. First of all.. Who is he? I .. Oh no you must be..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Raziel. I'm the love of your Mother there. It would do you well to remember who took care of your little ass, don't you think Kenshin?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then you are her, Isabella my mother. I'll ask you the same thing I asked him, but differently. Why didn't you kill the Ranger! You were a Knight, yet you couldn't beat A simple Ranger!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You couldn't beat a simple Cleric, Kenshin. Lets not forget. Does it matter?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why did you let me live, you must of known that I'd do nothing but lead you to destruction! Look at me now, is this what you wanted? A Weak child torn between two dieties?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Love, Kenshin. Love. I loved you from the first minute you came into the world. I couldn't kill my own child, whatever he came from. You were mine, not his. You do not remember what happened in the forest as you grew, don't you. I know why you are here. Now that you are done playing something that you are not, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Shintou</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, take me and Raziel's hand. I'll show you what you are.&quot; She spoke, softly extending a hand.. as did Raziel. Kenshin let his energy dispierse, watching the two of them extend their spectral hands to him. .. After careful consideration.. and a slight bit of hesitation.. he took them up upon it, he took their hands.<br>
<br>
Then the world seemed to flash by him. Millions upon millions of specs of light passed by all, images, memories, scenes and people.<br>
<br>
&quot;That Yotoden guy did a good job locking up what resided within your heart, kid. Do you remember being just a light hearted child, playing and playing with anything and everything? Raziel hated it, of course. Every day he'd consider just burning you into a corspe and ending your life. He did not like you much, that your stepfather didn't.. but I kept him back. For I loved you. Your play was that of a boy exploring the world. But their was more then that. As much time as you spent out in the woods, Raziel has you figured for a Ranger when you grew older. But I knew better, Kenshin. The father is always watching, and he has a plan for us all.&quot; <br>
<br>
She said as scenes of a young boy, strands of blonde and wihte intermixed within his mat of hair, and his eyes still of dark green pools. The young boy ran about, here and there playing and toying with everything. From the rocks on the ground to the bugs on the trees, to even the Black Wolves that would chase him, trying to end his young life. He just laughed and smiled at all of it, as it was just a fun game to him. Not a malious bond in his body. Not a single drop of hate in this pure spritited child.<br>
<br>
&quot;But.. why did Innoruuk allow me to become a ShadowKnight.. from what you are showing me, I'm nothing but a druid with blue skin, that I am!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But their was also these things.&quot; Raziel stepped foward as more scenes flashed.. flashing to the boy trying to take at his mothers sword. <br>
<br>
&quot;Ivy wasn't the only reason I did not slay you, Kenshin. I hated you, for you were the reason we lived out in the forest in shame, and not in the glory of the City. But, look at you trying to .. &quot;<br>
<br>
And with his words, the scene showed the kid Kenshin trying to wield a sword that was much larger then he was. He'd just stumble and fall, stagger and drop. Once, he almost got it, holding the sword at an downward angle and controling his balance.. just to swing and fall to the ground with in a heap.<br>
<br>
&quot;You'd always do this everytime Ivy left you alone. You even talked about it, to yourself. Always with the 'I want to be a fighter.' 'I want to be the strongest.' and such.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Even still, Paladins may enjoy fighting, and the Lightbringers, they are stronger then anyone else in the world, and that they will always be, that they shall.&quot;<br>
<br>
Raziel had only one word for that. <br>
<br>
&quot;Does it make you angry that they are?&quot;<br>
<br>
The look on Kenshin's face was that of a man snapped to reality.<br>
<br>
&quot;You followed and studied on Lanys T'Vyl, did you not Kenshin? This here, all of this is just another part of your past. Do you think Tier'dal come out of the womb with a sword and a hand full of hate? Even we aren't that blessed. Shintou, you refer to it as a mask. An alter ego. It was created out of your hate. Do you remember watching us die?<br>
<br>
No, you do not.. You were Shintou long before Yotoden even touched you.&quot; Raziel said as he began to show scenes of a more.. brutal fashion.<br>
<br>
Isabella hated these scenes, the ones which showed them lying there, lifeless before a crying child. A Crying Kenshin. The Rivers of blood extended right to his knees, his mother, his father for all he knew. Slain by those two guards.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is where he saved you, that Yotoden feller. He killed those two, but you watched us die. Don't doubt yourself so much, kid. You wanted to fight, heck its all you talked about. Don't lose yourself in the insanity and rage of it all so much however, your trueness resides in finding that boy, and finding also Shintou. Maybe meeting somewhere in the middle? Thats where you'll probably find Kenshin. Shintou is just as much apart of you as that boy is. He is as much as your past as what I've shown you here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But we cannot show you who you are. You have to find that for yourself, my son&quot; Isabella continued. &quot;Remember the Father is always watching. Heh, you were so much like Raziel. Love is for the weak? Innoruuk still blesses Tier'dal, even if they do love. Look at all of our followers that do. You were too.. too far. You wore Shintou like a mask to protect your feelings, instead of .. taking his soul into your own, where it should be. Kenshin, this child, new, nieve' and innocent is apart of you.. but so is the fighting, the hate, and the slaughter.<br>
<br>
Well.. where they all fit in your life.. thats what you have to find out for yourself, yes? ..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I.. .. I have alot of Meditation to do that I ..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, Not Meditation. Thinking.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;..Thinking.. Then.. that is what I shall do. That I shall&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Goodbye, Kenshin. Visit anytime, like the Father, we'll always be watching you.&quot; Isabella spoke her goodbyes as a flash of light engulfed the area..<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
Kenshin awoke, laying on the ground of the forest. He wasn't in the dishonored gravesite anymore.. but he was laying simply out in the middle of Nektulos. <br>
<br>
..The tools were in his hands.. now he just had to find the way to place them all together. <br>
<br>
..&quot;Whatever happens, happens.. I still fear if I do find myself.. will I like what I find.. what if I find out I'm no different then the elves that join guilds like &quot;Peacekeepers Alliance?&quot; .. No. I cannot worry about that.. whatever happens, happens. If I .. really don't settle this..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I can never fight again at all.. that I cannot.&quot;<br>
<br>
So he sat there.. and began to put the pieces together..<br>
What would he find? What would he create? ...Who knows..<br>
<br>
Fin.. that it is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kullgendphlith>Kullgen dPhlith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~subacca/spin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NOT A MAN</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/7/03 3:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~subacca/come_here.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Halfbreed for a reason. To go out like Mother.</span><hr size=1> /bump<br>
