Part 4.<br>
Soul and Sword..<br>
<br>
The Nektulos forest was uncharistically cool that night when Kenshin set himself down to meditate, taking his Katana and sending it into the earth before him. The days events was full of travel and exploration, not of the world but of his feelings. Pushing himself to odd situations produces the feelings that would guide him to what he was, truly. <br>
<br>
Their was always that druid girl, she let him run in the Forest of Kelethin with her, playing with the fay drakes and faries about. Such a tranquil existance brought peace and happyness. Contemptment, for in this world he didn't have to worry about swords or battles. No more slaughter and death, and no more futile fight against those who held power over all, those who took the stance of Neutrality and accepted all races, creeds, and religions to gain ultimate power.<br>
<br>
This peaceful feeling was somewhat of a release .. but as he continued to fly about, playing with the fay and watching the druid's magics to bring the forest alive.. the more he felt .. ackward. The happyness of the forest made him uneasy, and the bouncyness of that druid espically did not let him be at ease. He tried his best to pretend that he was not bothered by anything of this sort, but it did dawn on him as he slept that night, the Druid making a camp for them deep within the Faydark.<br>
<br>
&quot;I forced myself to ..endure this?&quot; his mind rang clearly as the realization settled in. Whatever the cause.. the days and nights he spent in the Faydark ended bringing him peace, but began to take something from him. Something that he did not want to lose at all.<br>
<br>
He had experenced as much as much as the Faydark as he wanted to. That night he was seen turning the page in the Book of Knowledge, that which would wisp him away to the Plane of the same name. It was then when he saw the armor clad fighters, going off to various places to fight and adventure when he realized what that forest and Tunare herself tried to take from him.<br>
<br>
He walked throught that plane, heading for the Nexus. He had another experence to encounter. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;..Its him. Shintou? What are you doing here of all places?&quot; Zharra said, seeing him come down the hall in the Plane of Knowledge. Mudwart simply nodded his troll head as Faentriel scowled at him, as expected. <br>
<br>
&quot;I've come to go to the Dragon Crypt with you all if you would have me, that I am. That is, if you do not mind me comming that is.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sure weez have yoos Shinny! Come on!&quot; Mudwart cheered as Kenshin walked past him.<br>
<br>
&quot;The name is Kenshin, that it is.&quot; Kenshin corrected the Troll.<br>
<br>
&quot;Trash.&quot; muddered Faentriel, still glaring at the object of her hate. It was just then when a Female Bard, halfelven of the Court of Crosswinds appeared before Mudwart, hugged him tightly, then ran off swiftly. Mudwart simply smiled to the attention.<br>
<br>
&quot;Trash you speak of me, that you do, however, your very husband is allowed to hug with Bards, that he is.&quot; Kenshin replied. Faentriel still scowed as they were teleported off.. on the trek to the Dragon Crypt.<br>
<br>
And so it began, all gathered within that old Crypt and the fighting began. Undead Dragons, Ratmen, small swarming bugs, snakes and all the like attacked them without mercy. Kenshin had his blade ready, it was as if he was awaiting this moment ever since he threw off the shell of Shintou. Fighting and slaughtering along side his comerads, his blade hot with the blood of his opponets. Many beings of the Nercopolis died that day due to their fighting, and this is where Kenshin found himself at home. Yes, it was hard for him to first draw his blade and fight, but once he drew it, the rest came Naturally. The Cut, the slash, the kill, even the Hate all returned. It was comforting, almost to be back in the state of combat, sword, hate, and comerads beside him. This is what came naturally to him, the fighting. The forest was comforting for a time, but after a while he became uneasy with it. Their was no uneasyness in this battle however, just fighting and fighting. <br>
<br>
But he did not find what truly shocked him untill after that battle was done. The finish of that assult led him back to his place in the Overthere.. well, on the way there..<br>
<br>
Until he ran into one little Paladin that Shintou had crossed in the past. A Elf named Korhil. The Hated Rival.<br>
<br>
The elf cared not about his problem. His 'Soul Searching'. The Paladin stood before the one, no matter his personality defects, that killed his child. This drove the Paladin deep within his vengeful hate and forced him to lash out against Kenshin.<br>
<br>
Kenshin acted as if he just wanted to fight for the challenge of battle, but he could feel those words being forced over his tounge, repressing what he wished to say.<br>
<br>
Unforutunity for Korhil, Shintou had been training while he fell in death, and fell behind. Kenshin, using these skills masterfully out danced the paladin in the fight, bringing him down with some effort, yes, but not with his full potiental. Watching the paladin cry out in pain from every slash was a .. dare I say it?<br>
A Joy for him. He felt the edge of his sword cut throught bone and flesh and it was a feeling that brought him to the realization.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is the end for you, that it is.&quot; Kenshin spoke as Korhil struggled to stand up on his feet, cut and battered from the battle, he knew he was in a kill or be killed situation.<br>
<br>
Had this been a fight purly to test skill, Kenshin would of just left him there. He had already bested him.<br>
<br>
But thats not Kenshin's way.<br>
<br>
&quot;You will die now, that you shall. Malious.. Hand!&quot; Kenshin shouted, his fist glowing in a rageful green light. It burned brighter then ever before, even Shintou's Malious Hand of Lanys T'Vyl was no match. This is because the trueness of his sprit was in that hand, in that punch that tore open Korhil's chest...<br>
<br>
And in the release of energy that blew the elven body apart from the inside out, leaving only streams of blood to run down the helm of Kenshin. That battle began him down the right track to see..<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
So here he is now, Meditating... his eyes slowly opening as the meditation comes to a close.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am Shintou, and he is me. That he is. .. Our sprits aren't seperated.. but they are intertwined.. I believe. Either. . really not able to exist with..<br>
<br>
Without the other.&quot;<br>
Fin.<br>
