Part 5 -Final- (Somewhat Disturbing Images of Suffering, you've been warned. Not for the easily offended.)<br>
The armor we all wear to protect what we care deeply about.<br>
<br>
..The memories returned throught meditation. Unlocking the secrets of what was within him, slowly they began to flood his mind. Remembering his parents, remembering being a child again.. and remembering what Shintou had protected him from. The Darkerside of his childhood.. the side that his parents didn't show him the other day.<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
&quot;Raziel!~ Stop it thats enought!' Isabella cried out, tackling her husband to the earth. She had stumbled upon one of the many times Raziel had gotten to be alone with the halfbreed discrase he had to endure as his own 'stepson'. The boy of 4 was tied to a crusifix, that is to take two sticks in the form of a cross, then tie a person to the newly formed Cross renduring them helpless to any attack your cruel mind can think of. In this instance, young Kenshin was the target of his stepfathers cruelity.. his wrath brought on by being unable to have a pure son of his own.<br>
<br>
For after the Incident, Isabella never wished to copoulate ever again, the scars rung too deeply to ever engage in that act ever again. Raziel brought it all upon that child, whenever Isabella left them alone long enought, he took to his act, using his ice based spells to blast the helpless child, usign weak ones not to kill him, but to make the boy suffer throught the cold bite of his spells. The icy hate of Innoruuk was too much for little Kenshin to bear. The Child could not take such beatings, day in and day out.<br>
<br>
But Shintou could.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
The mind is an amazing organ, something so complex that hardly anyone truly understands all of its marvels. Even the one marvel of why it splits to protect itself from the extreme trauma that would only lead a person down a life of depression and dispear. Forming an entirely new ego out of the first, leaving nothing but sufferage and depression in the viod. Concieved by pain of ones own father. Birthed throught the observation of ones own parents death. Shaped throught the training of a man gone mad. These are the things that formed the ego known to the world only as Shintou Shinai. The man that could master hate, yet that couldn't handle defeat and failure.<br>
<br>
These things forced Shintou to fall into that void between egos, that viod of depression and self hatred. He was so unlike the ego that first created him.. Kenshin. The boy that survived only because the love of his mother. Kenshin began to see himself as he really was.. and because of that he truly understood Shintou as well. He took the pain and the memories from him and hid them deeply within that third ego of depression. Like a Protective shell saving him.. but thats not what Kenshin wanted.<br>
<br>
Finally he felt the pain of loss for himself. The resentment for what he was, why it caused his own father to strike at him out of hate. Why he had to watch his own family die because of what he was.<br>
<br>
These things rushed over him, finally unprotected from them by Shintou, he felt true hatred for himself. It was as if he was becomming that ego himself.. but then.<br>
<br>
He remembered. He refocused himself on the true problem, on how to deal with that void.. why was it still there?<br>
Had he not found out who he was.. and why it was such? All should be well.. right?.. No..<br>
<br>
Then he remembered. The crimes of Shintou.<br>
Not against life.. Kenshin knew he enjoyed killing those bastards who probably forsaked him just as his father did and those Guards that killed his parents before his young eyes as much as Shintou did. But their was one thing that he couldn't forgive himself for.<br>
The crimes against love. Those women foolish to fall in love with Shintou only were met with his words, and his unliving heart of stone. &quot;Love is for the weak.&quot; His words of sufferage to them.<br>
And with his own words he tormented and shattered the latest victum of this string of torment.<br>
<br>
The time for Meditation was over. He rose up, Kenshin did.. bearing the soul of Shintou as his armor and sword, that he did. Already he decided that it would be best to co-exist with his alter, letting their souls merge as one being, that being the only way that he could escape the viod of depression. Together they would make up for the short commings each had, together they would find strenght that they neither could find alone.<br>
<br>
And together, for their first task.. they would have to find her. Their was much to make up for.<br>
